# Google OAuth Configuration (for Admin access only)
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your-google-oauth-client-id-here

# Admin Configuration
VITE_ADMIN_EMAILS=admin@example.com,another-admin@example.com

# Instructions for Netlify Deployment:
# 1. Go to your Netlify site dashboard
# 2. Navigate to Site settings > Environment variables
# 3. Add the following variables:
#    - VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID: Your Google OAuth Client ID
#    - VITE_ADMIN_EMAILS: Comma-separated list of admin emails
# 4. Redeploy your site for changes to take effect

# Instructions for Local Development:
# 1. Copy this file to .env (remove .example)
# 2. Go to https://console.developers.google.com/
# 3. Create a new project or select existing one
# 4. Enable Google+ API
# 5. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials
# 6. Add your domain to authorized origins
# 7. Copy the client ID and paste it above
# 8. Add authorized admin email addresses (comma-separated)

# Note: Netlify environment variables take priority over .env file values